<step1>
<ptxt>CONSTRUCTION</ptxt>
<step2>
<ptxt>Cylinder Head Cover</ptxt>
<step3>
<ptxt>The cylinder head cover is made of plastic to reduce weight and noise.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>Acrylic rubber, which excels in heat resistance and reliability, is used for the cylinder head cover gasket.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>Baffle plates made of plastic are provided inside the cylinder head cover to reduce the consumption of engine oil through blow-by gas. The baffle plates are welded onto the cylinder head cover, and cannot be removed.</ptxt>
