<step2>
<ptxt>Crankshaft and Crankshaft Bearing</ptxt>
<step3>
<ptxt>The crankshaft has 5 journals and 8 balance weights.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>All pin and journal fillets are roll-finished to maintain adequate strength.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>The crankshaft bearing is made of aluminum alloy.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>The crankshaft bearing caps are tightened using 2 plastic region tightening bolts for each journal.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>Similar to the connecting rod bearings, the lining surface of the crankshaft bearings has been micro-grooved to achieve an optimal amount of oil clearance. As a result, cold-engine cranking performance has been improved and engine vibrations have been reduced.</ptxt>
</step3>
<step3>
<ptxt>The upper main bearing has an oil groove around its inside circumference.</ptxt>
